==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: earth-born
<hw>earth"-born</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦etil⟧rth"b⟦ocir⟧rn`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Born of
the earth; terrigenous; springing originally from the earth; human;
having the characteristics of earthly life; <as>as, <ex>earth-born</ex>
beings</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some <qex>earthborn</qex> giant.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Relating to, or occasioned by, earthly
objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All <qex>earthborn</qex> cares are wrong.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Earthbred</ent>⟦br⟧
